                <note rend="inline" type="source">667n.113/3: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kellogg</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-12-11T16:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 11, 1924—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 11—2:23 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>516. The Foreign Office inquires whether in view of the signature of the
                    Palestine mandate convention you now desire to pursue the questions raised
                    concerning increased customs duty in Palestine and the attachment of the bank
                    account of Skora; see your telegrams 315, September 2, 4 p.m. and 365, October
                    18, 2 p.m. The Foreign Office suggests that although the points raised are still
                    under consideration by His Majesty’s Government, their importance is no longer
                    such as to warrant continuance of the correspondence.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
